commit.message:
Remove CODEOWNERS (#34)

The CODEOWNERS file was an attempt to setup a fine grained permission model
unfortunately GitHub does not support this model as it requires all changes
to go through an pull request to be enforced. We consider this too much
friction.

Additionally the requirement for a pull request prevents Renovate from pushing
changes directly to main. This generates notification spam.

commit.message:
Run tests in GitHub Actions (#23)

* Add files for running tests in GitHub Actions

* Use README badge for GitHub Actions CI

* Remove Travis CI config

* Remove Gemfile.lock from git

* Fix deprecation warning from bundler

* Better failure summary

* Ignore Mac temp files

* Add source to Gemfile

* Allow some tests to be skipped if the don't apply

It seems that Test::Unit 2.x doesn't work with newer Rubies

See https://github.com/test-unit/test-unit/commit/7c93699e92ebb05fe0d68e2df1a99774a721aa92

* Show command output to help debugging failures in CI

* Try to see if this fixes the build

* Use env var to specify bundle path

* Try doing `bundle update` first

* Try turning off bundler cache

* Split up install and test commands so we can see what's going on

* Print command being run

* Try a bundle clean too

* Try another way to specify the bundle path

* Don't use bundle_path - rely on config

* Try to reset GitHub's cache

* Make sure we fail if bundle install fails

* Make output easier to scan

* Try this to bust the cache

* Try to fail early if bundle install command fails

* Dump bundler config

* Clearly print all output

* Print bundler config in CI step

* Clearer logging of output

* Don't be so fancy

* Bring back the lockfiles

I'm wondering if this will help CI to install things

* Try using a matrix

* Just try one scenario

* Fix substitution

* Install gem in GitHub Actions

* Run all bundle commands on the matrix Gemfile

* bash

* Use bash to iterate and test scenarios for a Gemfile

* Add remaining Gemfiles to matrix

* Ensure we check for empty output too

* Use new bash test script

* Remove Ruby test script

* Tidy up

* Add a comment
